  "decision_conditions": [
    "<p><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-a1a13ab6-7fff-c0dd-0495-fb323e06a4cd\"><span style=\"font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline;\">The proposed roof terrace, by virtue of its detailed design and position, would result in the introduction of an incongruous addition to the roof of the three storey outrigger that fails to respect the character and appearance of the subject building and wider terrace. As such,&nbsp; the proposal is contrary to </span><span style=\"font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline;\">The London Plan (2021) policy D4 (Delivering good design), and policy LP1 (Design quality and local character) of Hackney's Local Plan 2033 (2020) and the relevant sections of Hackney's Residential Extensions and Alterations Supplementary Planning Document (2009). </span></span><br></p>",
    "&lt;p&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;docs-internal-guid-cfd23d0a-7fff-4a2b-dc5e-ca2b2f0b1122&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline;&quot;&gt;The proposed rear roof extension, by reason of its scale, bulk, positioning, and detailed design, is an overly large and dominant extension,&amp;nbsp; that fails to be sufficiently set down from the ridge, up from the eaves and in from the party walls, and by reason of its proportions is not considered to be good design. The proposal is therefore contrary to The London Plan (2021) policy D4 (Delivering good design), and policy LP1 (Design quality and local character) of Hackney&#x27;s Local Plan 2033 (2020) and the relevant sections of Hackney&#x27;s Residential Extensions and AlterationsSupplementary Planning Document (2009). &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;"
  ],
